\cf0 FAQ (Frequently asked questions)\

\fs22 \ulnone \
(Q) : LaTeXiT crashes on launch.\
(R) : A corrupted history or library may prevent LaTeXiT from launching. In such a case, just move around the files "history.dat" and "library.latexlib" that lie in the folder "Library/Application Support/LaTeXiT" of your home folder.\
\
(Q): where can I get pdflatex, dvipdf and ghostscript ?\
(A): please see the section "Install Latex" of this document.\
\
(Q) : I did install LaTeX the way described, but LaTeXiT seems not be functional either.\
(R) : If you have installed TeXShop, then LaTeXiT, then LaTeX, the paths of LaTeXiT may point to a pdflatexc of TeXShop that is not sufficient. Just try before to remove LaTeXiT's Preferences (Library/Preferences/fr.club.ktd.LaTeXiT.plist). You can also try to set by hand the paths in the "composition" pane of the LaTeXiT's preferences.\
\
(Q): My equation is cut and does not display completely .\
(A): See the "Known issues" section below.\
\
(Q): Which export format should I prefer ?\
(A): PDF is usually the best choice, since it is a "vectorial" format : the image can be resized without loss of quality.\
\
(Q): changes to the preamble seems not take effect unless I quit and restart the application.\
(A): Any modification to the default preamble does not affect currently open windows, since their would be the risk to overwrite some modifications the user has made in them. However, you do not have to restart the application; just open a new document like in any application (\uc0\u8984 N).\

\fs26 \ul \

\fs22 \ulnone (Q): LinkBack does not work when I use the LaTeXiT's service.\
(A): See section "Known issues" for more details. To solve this problem, try to disable the baseline alignment of the equation in the LaTeXiT's service preferences.\
\
(Q): I don't understand the "encapsulation" palette.\
(R): This palette fills a very particular need. Usually, it is useless to drag'n drop an equation (as an image) towards an application that cannot display images. However, if this application is a LaTeX text editor, it may be relevant to drag'n drop some text related to the equation : its source code, a \\ref\{\} with its title.... So, this is customizable in the palette, and will work for drag'n drop from the library.\
