\fs22 \ulnone \
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\qj

\f2\b \cf0 - if you only have TeXShop, LaTeXiT cannot function properly. You need a real LaTeX installation. You will find more information in the next section "Install LaTeX";\
- if you ever notice some random font change in the generated images, this seems to occur when the history becomes corrupted. Just clean up your history, this should make the problem disappear. It has also been reported that third-party Open-Type fonts could cause problems;\
- if you notice that LaTeXiT, even when not used, eats some processor time an consumes more and more memory, just be aware that to speed up its launch time, it loads the images of the history in the background. This task has a very low priority and may take some time; however, it will stabilize. If you really want to avoid it, just think to clean up your history from time to time!\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\qj

\f1\b0 \cf0 - when the equation color is set to perfect white, the equation seems ill-cropped (left and right parenthesis may disappear for instance). This is a bug of ghostscript, that fails at cropping well with a white equation on a white background. To fix that, use an "almost white" margin, or use the "Palettes > Margins" menu to increase left and right margins;\
- syntax colouring does not handle "$$" well;\
- with very little equations, you may encounter a cropping problem. LaTeX may fail to compute the bounding box of an equation. There are two workarounds : either add margins with the Margin palette, or use $$...$$ in TEXT mode instead of using DISPLAY or INLINE mode (there is an internal difference in LaTeXiT);\
- custom margins are not taken in account when exporting to EPS; it seems to be a bug of GhostScript;\
- while evolving from version 1.2 for Panther to 1.3 for Panther, you need to rename the folder ~/Library/LaTeXiT-panther into ~/Library/LaTeXiT, to get back your history and library;\
- the service does not work with Mail 2.0.0, ..., 2.1 (latest available version at the moment these lines are written);\
- the service does not work with Keynote 1, 2, 3 & 4, since Keynote cannot insert an image into a block of text; as a workaround, you can set in the Preferences, pane "Services", to register service calls in the history. That way, even if the service fails at inserting an image, this one becomes available in the history window, that could have been put in some corner for easy access;\
- LinkBack may not work when using LaTeXiT's service. Indeed, to align the equation with the surrounding text, LaTeXiT embbeds the image in an RTFD stream, so that it can tune the baseline. However, it may happen that text editors fails "extracting" the image from the stream. So, even if the display is correct, LinkBack becomes "unreachable". The culprit in this case is the text editor, but it is something difficult. To solve the problem, disable the "alignement of the equation with the surrounding text" in the LaTeXiT's service preferences; this turns off baseline tuning and do not use RTFD streams;\
- with Pages 1.0.2 and 2.0.1, when using the LaTeXiT service, the automatic shift of the equation, in order to align it on the line ("baseline" management), seems not to work. However, it works well with TextEdit and Nisus Writer Express, so it is certainly a bug of Pages.\
- with EazyDraw 1.7.1, drag'n dropped equations are displayed upside-down. This is a bug of EazyDraw, that has been fixed in the 1.8 version;\
- with Adobe Illustrator, if you drag'n drop a PDF equation from LaTeXiT to Illustrator, the font will be changed, because Illustrator can edit each symbol of the PDF generated by LaTeXiT, and uses its own fonts. To avoid that, use a temporary file: drag the equation from LaTeXiT to your desktop, a file is created, and drop this file into your Illustrator's document. It works, but then you won't be able to edit the equation in Illustrator any more. Other possibility: export with another format (see LaTeXiT Preferences), like EPS, or PDF with outlined fonts;\
- still with Adobe Illustrator, when drag'n dropping in it, a file may be created on the Desktop. It only occurs with Illustrator, and he is mostly responsible, because of its way to handle drag'n drop. Such problems do not occur with OmniGraffle;\
- still with Adobe Illustrator : many glitches reported by users are solved by upgrading Illustrator to a newer version;\
- you can notice that in the system console log, a message appears at each latexisation : "WARNING: Type1 font data returned by OFAStreamPSDownload isn't in the correct format required by the Adobe Type 1 Font Format specification". You can safely ignore this warning, which is due to the pdf files generated by pdflatex. In practice there are no problems, and it may even disappear in future versions of pdflatex (but I don't know, in fact).\
